@page "/"

<PageTitle>Zombie Simulation</PageTitle>

<div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 20px; text-align: center;">
    <h1 style="color: #4CAF50; font-size: 3rem;">Zombie Simulation</h1>
    <h3 style="color: #555; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        Welcome to the Configurable Zombie Simulation!
    </h3>

    <div style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
        <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #333;">
            In this interactive simulation, humans and zombies move around a dynamic environment. 
            Humans try to survive by avoiding zombies, while zombies relentlessly pursue humans to infect them. 
            Watch how different strategies play out in real time as the simulation evolves. Can the humans escape, 
            or will the zombie horde take over? Experiment with various parameters and witness the chaos unfold!
        </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 30px; text-align: center;">
        <img src="/Images/Sim.png" alt="Simulation Preview" 
             style="max-width: 100%; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);">
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 40px; padding: 20px; background-color: #f1f1f1; border-radius: 10px;">
        <h2 style="color: #333;">About the Developers</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #555; margin-bottom: 10px;">
            This project was developed by <strong>Daniel Marin</strong> and <strong>Jennifer Vicentes</strong>, 
            third-year students at <strong>Texas Tech University</strong>. As passionate learners in Object-Oriented Programming, 
            we created this simulation to showcase our skills in design patterns, and interactive UI design.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #555;">
            Thank you for exploring our work, and we hope you enjoy the experience!
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
